      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Before data can be opened in the specXplore dashboard, it needs to be processed using the specXplore importing pipeline... Spectral data are imported into Python using matchms, and basic specXplore data processing is performed... Spectral data can then be used to initialize a template specXplore object that automatically computes pairwise spectral similarities",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes initialization of specXplore objects from raw spectral data via the importing pipeline, not from saved session data objects loaded from disk. The paper does not explicitly address session persistence/loading from disk.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c04444",
