    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Embeddings produced by t-SNE are built to preserve local neighborhoods in the high-dimensional space in their projection to a two-dimensional space.24 This focus may lead to difficulties in interpretation of t-SNE results as neglect of global similarity preservation may render cluster proximity a poor indicator of cluster similarity.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms t-SNE preserves local neighborhoods but explicitly notes that t-SNE does NOT preserve global similarity well. The card claims t-SNE preserves 'local and global spectral relationships,' but the paper states t-SNE has a 'local focus' and may neglect 'global similarity preservation.' This is a partial match\u2014the tool does preserve local relationships but not global ones as claimed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c04444",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have a precomputed similarity matrix of mass spectra (e.g., ms2deepscore-based similarities) and need to generate a low-dimensional (2-D) interactive overview representation that preserves local and global spectral relationships for exploratory dashboard visualization or",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:17.745264+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The central overview of specXplore is based on a t-SNE embedding of the ms2deepscore pairwise similarity matrix serving as the primary similarity score.",
      "asbval:note": "Scope is consistent with paper's use of t-SNE on high-dimensional similarity matrices; the 'when NOT to use' criterion is logically sound.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c04444",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input spectral data is already in 2-D or lower-dimensional representation; t-SNE is unnecessary.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:17.745264+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "However, ms2deepscore may also introduce a much denser topology. At many reasonable threshold levels, node-link diagram representations of dense matrices tend to become unreadable for the network as a whole.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that t-SNE is used with dense similarity matrices (ms2deepscore produces dense topology), supporting the 'when NOT to use' criterion for sparse matrices.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c04444",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Similarity matrix is sparse or contains many zero/missing values; t-SNE requires dense distance estimates.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:17.745264+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For the wheat data set, the pipeline preprocessing time was less than 15 min... the processing time for the larger urine data set was less than 75 min, whereof approximately 62 min was taken up by MS2Query and 9 min for all pairwise spectral similarity computations.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates that t-SNE computation is part of a batch preprocessing pipeline with significant computational cost, supporting the 'when NOT to use' criterion for real-time/streaming scenarios.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c04444",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Real-time or streaming spectral data processing is required; t-SNE is computationally expensive and unsuitable for incremental updates.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:17.745264+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The t-SNE embedding overview panel of specXplore provides the user with an abstract and condensed representation of the pairwise similarity matrix lacking a clear node grouping structure.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes t-SNE as providing an 'abstract' representation, supporting the claim that t-SNE axes are not directly interpretable.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c04444",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tsne-embedding-dimensionality-reduction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Quantitative interpretation of individual axis values is needed; t-SNE axes are arbitrary and not interpretable as physical or chemical scales.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:58:17.745264+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
